 ('339', 'field', '11', 'en_us', ' my name is chris uhler and i m a user experience designer at ideabase i m also a graduate student in kent state s user experience design program ideabase has been a great opportunity for gaining real world experience personally i ve been learning a ton from my manager chris hallahan he is a super awesome resource and it s truly rewarding to be able to work on a project the whole way through before i started at ideabase in march i actually had no idea this place even existed until my co worker at bent tree coffee roasters told me about it i ve been working at bent tree also here in kent for two years as a production manager but i m glad i found out about ideabase because it s a great starting point for my future in the user experience design field my main client right now is northeast ohio medical university i am working on a competitive analysis for them in support of their future website redesign a competitive analysis is basically the process of looking at similar websites and analyzing their strengths and weaknesses i ve also created and sent out a survey to get feedback on the current site and i ll be analyzing the data when the survey closes i stay super busy with work and school but in my spare time i enjoy photography home brewing and my motorcycle recently i made a kolsch brew which is a light sweet beer i think it turned out pretty well i needed a break from the heavy stuff and this was a nice alternative right now i m just super excited to get married in the fall my fiance and i have been together about 5 years we actually met at kent state and have been together ever since overall i am just excited for the experience at ideabase i know i will be able to learn a lot here and can use this experience as a good foundation for my future '),
