 ('380', 'field', '6', 'en_us', ' executive vice president greg kiskadden oversees whitespace creative new business development he draws from his rich leadership background to foster key relationships with prospective clients from a diverse body of industries such as service manufacturing logistics healthcare and higher education he also supports comprehensive agency operations including spearheading workflow and scheduling improvements and assisting in overall agency integration a member of whitespace since 1996 greg has transitioned from a designer and developer to account supervisor and agency executive vice president experience in these varied roles has enabled greg to combine his talents in developing integrated communication programs with extensive client service and sales expertise it also has allowed him to view projects from a unique perspective one that blends strategic marketing and tactical execution to support business goals prior to whitespace greg worked at the little tikes company a division of rubbermaid in hudson ohio where he helped develop product literature for domestic and international sales print collateral and advertising material a kent state graduate he earned a ba in visual communications with a concentration in illustration and art history greg currently serves on the habitat for humanity public relations and communications board as well as on the professional advisory board of ideabase a kent state university student run marketing communications firm in kent ohio greg is an avid runner and in addition to competing in the akron and nashville half marathons he coaches cross country for st patrick school in kent ohio he enjoys travel and has journeyed to italy belize trinidad tobago and puerto rico greg lives in kent with his wife and two daughters '),
